Nairobi Governor Dr Evans Kidero today became the first Governor to petition the Senate. He made an appearance before the Justice and Legal Affairs Committee.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Kidero made the petition to the Senate concerning payment due to the NCCG on account of a parcel of land in Embakasi allocated to the Department of Defence.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; The Governor is demanding Kes 61.5B from the Department of Defence.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Dr Kidero called upon the Senate to enact a legislation setting out a procedure for amicable and expeditious resolutions of disputes between the National and County governments. To avoid lengthy and costly litigation processes between the two levels of Government.